\begin_layout Standard
Localised environments are used to inform the computer that here are specific bits and pieces of text that serve a specific purpose and thus need to be layouted in a particular way.
 Some localised environments occur many times in a document – like (sub)headings,
 lists or tables – while others only apply to one specific word – like an italicised term 
