literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\series bold
All
\series default
 local environments share that they take basic layouting instructions from the global settings;
 the caption of an illustration 
\series bold
will
\series default
 use the basic document font just the same as a table unless specified otherwise.
 Emphasised text,
 whether that is italics,
 boldface or colours,
 are added 
\series bold
on top
\series default
 of those global layouting instructions.
 Thus,
 when you change the document font from Times New Roman to Arial,
 you won't lose your italics,
 they will simply appear as italicised text in Arial now.
\end_layout

